"It looks like it," said I ruefully, pointing to a huge bundle in the corner. "I have had nothing
else to do."

"It is fortunate, for you will perhaps be able to post me up. I read nothing except the criminal
news and the agony column. The latter is always instructive. But if you have followed recent events
so closely you must have read about Lord St. Simon and his wedding?"

"Oh, yes, with the deepest interest."